# HCMUS GPA UI Rules

- Use HCMUS GPA design tokens before adding new colors, spacing, fonts, shadows, or motion.
- Use `--brand-*`, `--surface-*`, `--line*`, `--focus-ring`, and shared UI primitives before writing new Tailwind one-off styles.
- Keep user-facing copy in Vietnamese with full diacritics.
- Do not expose database or implementation language in student-facing UI.
- Use HCMUS blue as the primary brand language; reserve high-chroma accents for actions or states.
- Use official HCMUS logo assets only from `public/brand/`, without recoloring, stretching, cropping, or redrawing.
- Prefer clear, breathable dashboards with stable grids over generic landing-page sections.
- Build product-specific UI; do not copy external sites, UI kits, or AI-default gradients. Borrow principles, not layouts.
- New buttons, form fields, badges, cards, dropdowns, toasts, progress bars and tables must go through `components/ui/*` unless there is a documented exception.
- Motion must clarify state changes and respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Important long labels may truncate only when a tooltip/title or detail view reveals the full text.
- Run `npm run ui:audit` after UI changes.
